						<summary>

						<p>On a mutilated slab in front of the Śiva temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1170, <hi rend="italic">(bindu-turaṁga-rudra),</hi> Kīlaka, Māgha Śivarātri.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. Records the gift of a village to the temple of Sōmanātha at Anugupuraṁ by a certain Rājadaṇḍādhipati Mahādēvarāja. Eulogy of the military commander is interesting and requires a further study.</p>						

						</summary>
